abstract = {This chapter examines the current challenges in meeting key supply chain objectives and gives detailed descriptions of how blockchain can help firms achieve these objectives. Specifically, it looks at the following supply chain management (SCM) objectives: (a) Reducing costs; (b) Assuring quality of products; (c) Increasing speed; (d) Increasing dependability; (e) Reducing risks; (f) Facilitating sustainable practices; and (g) Enhancing flexibility. This chapter uses a number of practical applications and real-world examples to delve into blockchain's roles in contributing to these objectives. A key argument is that blockchain makes it possible to trace ingredients and components across multiple tiers of a supply chain because data must be shared in a tamperproof way and must be accessible to relevant parties. Blockchain, thus, facilitates traceability, which is among the key mechanisms by which blockchain can help firms meet the various supply chain objectives.}
